.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-checksum 1  "rom-weaver-checksum "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-checksum \- Compute checksums for files or selected container payloads
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver checksum\fR <\fB\-\-algo\fR> [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-select\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-rom\-filter\fR] [\fB\-\-log\-level\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-filter\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-extract\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-trim\-fix\fR] [\fB\-\-start\fR] [\fB\-\-length\fR] [\fB\-\-probe\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fISOURCE\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compute checksums for files or selected container payloads
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-algo\fR \fI<ALGO>\fR
Checksum algorithm; repeat for multiple algorithms
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-select\fR \fI<SELECT>\fR
Select a container payload by exact name, prefix, or glob (repeatable)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-rom\-filter\fR
Keep ROM\-like payload candidates during checksum auto\-extract
.TP
\fB\-\-log\-level\fR \fI<LOG_LEVEL>\fR
Set application log level (off, error, warn, info, debug, trace)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
off
.IP \(bu 2
error
.IP \(bu 2
warn
.IP \(bu 2
info
.IP \(bu 2
debug
.IP \(bu 2
trace
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-filter\fR
Keep patch\-like payload candidates during checksum auto\-extract
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-extract\fR
Disable container auto\-extract and checksum the source bytes directly
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Increase application log verbosity; repeat for debug and trace
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR
Disable default ignore filtering during checksum container payload resolution
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Show only application errors
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-trim\-fix\fR
Disable automatic trim\-boundary checksum fixes for trim\-eligible ROMs
.TP
\fB\-\-start\fR \fI<BYTE>\fR
Zero\-based byte offset at which hashing begins
.TP
\fB\-\-length\fR \fI<BYTES>\fR
Number of bytes to hash from \-\-start (defaults to the remaining input)
.TP
\fB\-\-probe\fR
Fold platform probe metadata into the result and fail when the checksummed bytes resolve to no known platform
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<auto|N>\fR [default: auto]
Thread budget: auto or a positive integer
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fISOURCE\fR>
File or container payload to checksum
